title: Groundwater Monitoring System 1994, Kansas
name: Groundwater Monitoring System 1994, Kansas
description:
Abstract: The coverages included in this data set are used to support water quality programs. The Lake Monitoring coverage, the Stream Monitoring System coverage, and the Groundwater Monitoring System coverage reference sampling locations across the state. The Lake Monitoring Chemical 1990-1994 coverage, the Stream Monitoring Chemical 1990-1995 coverage, and the Groundwater Monitoring Chemical 1990-1994 coverage reference chemical analysis at given sampling locations across the state. The coverage data is current as of publication date. The KDHE operational databases are dynamic databases. 
Purpose: The Lake Monitoring, the Stream Monitoring System, and the Groundwater Monitoring System coverages were developed to improve program staff reporting capabilities, to cross-reference these locations with EPA's hydrologic reach reference system, and to establish a stable reference for continued water monitoring assessment. The Lake Monitoring Chemical 1990-1994, the Stream Monitoring Chemical 1990-1995, and the Groundwater Monitoring Chemical 1990-1994 coverages were developed to improve program staff reporting capabilities and to establish a stable reference for continued water monitoring assessment.

Uploaded into Geocommons as shp, dbf, and shx files.
